long_desc.thetext:
Currently we have to remove bindings by previously saved binding ids. This makes code in some cases unnecessary complex. It would be useful to have a function to do so.


Example (function removeBindingsByTarget() is fictive): 

if (oldModel) {
  model.removeBindingsByTarget(this.__textArea);
  this.__textArea.removeBindingsByTarget(model);
}

if (model)
{
  model.bind("description", this.__textArea, "value");
  this.__textArea.bind("value", model, "description");
}

Furthermore it would be useful to remove by target object and property.

model.removeBindingsByTarget(this.__textArea, "description");
